(3290, '_transient_feed_88c95ea6746a99025a514512c65189e8', 'a:4:{s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"rss\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"2.0\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"channel\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Advanced Ads\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"https://wpadvancedads.com\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"Advanced Ads for WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:13:\"lastBuildDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 19 Dec 2017 13:01:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"language\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"generator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://wordpress.org/?v=4.9.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"item\";a:12:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Ads and security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-and-security/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 06 Nov 2017 10:53:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=88600\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:498:\"<p>Advanced Ads is restrictive about who can manage ads on your site. By default, this is only the admin. However, allowing all kinds of codes in the Plain Text ad type is still a risky business if you just copy and paste ad codes from external sources. I wanted to use this article to give [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-and-security/\">Ads and security</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Thomas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2785:\"<p>Advanced Ads is restrictive about who can manage ads on your site. By default, this is only the admin. However, allowing all kinds of codes in the <em>Plain Text</em> ad type is still a risky business if you just copy and paste ad codes from external sources. I wanted to use this article to give some advice on how to increase security when handling ads.</p>\n<h2>Sanitize input data</h2>\n<p>When you are writing your own code, especially PHP, then you should make sure that you don’t use data from sources that could be manipulated. At least sanitize these values with the appropriate <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Validating_Sanitizing_and_Escaping_User_Data\">functions WordPress provides</a>.</p>\n<p>You should also be aware that a broken PHP code can just break the frontend of your website.</p>\n<p>If you are not the only one working with ads on your site, you might want to set the <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">ADVANCED_ADS_DISALLOW_PHP</pre> constant in your <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">wp-config.php</pre> and disable the PHP option completely.</p>\n<h2>Secure ad networks</h2>\n<p>The biggest thread when running ads are codes from ad networks. There is a new ad network every other day, and it is hard to keep track on all of them. It happened more than once to me as a publisher that an ad network was not delivering the “secure” and “family friendly” ads they promised in the first place and instead displayed spammy ads to dubious URL on my websites.</p>\n<p>That might not be a security risk to you, but it is to your visitors, who might find your site a non-trustworthy resource when seeing those ads.</p>\n<h2>Limiting backend access</h2>\n<p>An obvious suggestion is not to give away backend access easily. I know that we are asking for it from time to time in support to speed up the process of helping you. It is on you to decide whether you trust us with that kind of access.</p>\n<p>In any case, you should never give away your personal account details and always create a new username for each entity with only the necessary capabilities. You should also remove the access when the work is done.</p>\n<h2>Passwords</h2>\n<p>It is not directly ad-related, but could indeed be the cause why your site suddenly shows content that wasn’t there before. When I was still working as a freelancer I had to clean up multiple sites from malicious code, and it always came through insecure passwords, especially to FTP accounts.</p>\n<p>WordPress already suggests better passwords, but make sure you also use complicated and long passwords for FTP accounts.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-and-security/\">Ads and security</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"How to add AdSense In-Feed to WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-adsense-in-feed-to-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 02 Nov 2017 08:16:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"AdSense\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=88018\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:355:\"<p>Learn how to place an AdSense In-feed ad between posts on your WordPress site without the need to code it yourself.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-adsense-in-feed-to-wordpress/\">How to add AdSense In-Feed to WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Thomas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11880:\"<p>In-feed ads are dedicated AdSense ad codes which you can place within lists of posts. While you could do this with the default content ad units as well, In-feed ad units come with a new layout and more options. I guess that together with the In-article ads they are going to replace the current display ads format.</p>\n<p>This tutorial is going to cover</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creating an In-feed ad in your AdSense account</li>\n<li>Moving that ad code to your WordPress site</li>\n<li>Placing the ad between posts</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Creating an AdSense In-feed ad</h2>\n<p>Follow these steps to create a new AdSense In-feed ad in your AdSense account.</p>\n<p>1. Log in and go to <em>My </em>ads<em> &gt; Ad units</em> and click on <em>New ad unit</em>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87874\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad.png\" alt=\"AdSense In-feed new ad navigation\" width=\"626\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad.png 626w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad-300x151.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad-60x30.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-new-ad-150x75.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 626px) 100vw, 626px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2. Choose the In-feed ad by clicking on <em>Select</em></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87875\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type.png\" alt=\"AdSense In-feed ad type option\" width=\"339\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type.png 339w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type-283x300.png 283w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type-57x60.png 57w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-type-142x150.png 142w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 339px) 100vw, 339px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3. If you see the introduction then go to the end of the slideshow and click on <em>Get Started</em></p>\n<p>4. Now choose the format. For desktop sites, I would choose one of the formats with the image on the left and text on the right side, while on smaller layouts the image at the top and text at the bottom might work best. You can later test other layouts as well.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-87876\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts-679x253.png\" alt=\"AdSense Infeed Layouts overview\" width=\"679\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts-679x253.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts-300x112.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts-60x22.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts-150x56.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-layouts.png 910w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>5. You now see multiple options on the left side of the screen. The most important are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ad unit name</strong> – enter the name of the ad, so that you can identify it later in the list of ads</li>\n<li><strong>Global Options &gt; Allow selected display ads</strong> – this will increase the number of ads bidding on your view and increase revenue. Switch it off if you only want to see the default In-feed layout format you choose earlier</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All the other options are more or less helping you to adjust the ad layout to your site. The more experienced you are with your ad setup, the more you can experiment and also <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-split-test-different-ad-positions/\">run tests</a> later.</p>\n<p>6. Click on <em>Save and get code</em></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87879\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-infeed-get-code.png\" alt=\"AdSense Infeed get code buttom\" width=\"134\" height=\"46\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-infeed-get-code.png 134w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-infeed-get-code-60x21.png 60w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 134px) 100vw, 134px\" /></p>\n<p>7. Get the code by clicking on the <em>COPY CODE SNIPPET</em> button</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-87882\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code-679x323.png\" alt=\"AdSense In-feed get the ad code\" width=\"679\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code-679x323.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code-300x143.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code-60x29.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code-150x71.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/adsense-in-feed-code.png 865w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can click on <em>I’m done</em> now and move to the implementation of the ad code into your site.</p>\n<p>The ad code is now stored in the clipboard on your computer. You could also save it in a .txt file if you don‘t intend to go to the next step right away.</p>\n<h2>Adding the In-feed ad to your WordPress site</h2>\n<p>Once you have the AdSense Infeed ad code, you need to place it between posts. Most websites not only list those on their homepage but also have archives by category or author.</p>\n<p>Our free <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-ads-adsense-in-feed/\">AdSense In-feed plugin</a> can help you place In-feed ads to your WordPress site without any coding. Just install the basic version of <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/how-to-install-advanced-ads/\">Advanced Ads</a> and this add-on.</p>\n<h3>1. Creating the AdSense ad</h3>\n<p>After you installed Advanced Ads, go to <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Ads</em> and click on <em>New Ad</em>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Enter a title for your ad – it is only visible to you.</li>\n<li>Select <em>AdSense ad</em> in the <em>Ad Type</em> box.</li>\n<li>Paste your AdSense code into the textarea in the <em>Ad Parameters</em> box.</li>\n<li>Click on <em>Get details</em>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The last step will import the details of the ad into Advanced Ads. The final setup might look like this:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-87883\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads-679x426.png\" alt=\"in-feed in Advanced Ads\" width=\"679\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads-679x426.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads-300x188.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads-60x38.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads-150x94.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/in-feed-advanced-ads.png 845w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>2. Placing the In-feed ad between posts</h3>\n<p>Now you define where the ad should show up.</p>\n<p>Advanced Ads separates content (ads) and positions (placements) to make you more flexible when it comes to rotating or replacing ads.</p>\n<p>Go to <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Placements</em>. If you already have placements then click on <em>New Placement</em> below the placement list.</p>\n<p>Choose the <em>AdSense In-feed</em> placement type with the following icon, enter a name for the placement and select the ad you want to display.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-86693\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed.png\" alt=\"AdSense In-feed position\" width=\"180\" height=\"135\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed.png 180w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-60x45.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-150x113.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 180px) 100vw, 180px\" /></p>\n<p>Save the new placement.</p>\n<p>After you saved it, search for the new placement in the list. Here you can select before which post in the frontend the ad should show up.</p>\n<p>The example below would show the ad between the first and second post on the homepage and other archive pages.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-87522 size-large\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement-679x136.png\" alt=\"AdSense Infeed placement optione\" width=\"679\" height=\"136\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement-679x136.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement-300x60.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement-60x12.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement-150x30.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/adsense-in-feed-placement.png 818w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You can repeat these steps with different placements if you want to place an ad between multiple posts and not just at one position.</p>\n<p>The ad code could be the same, but if you want to test at which position In-feed ads work best, then I would suggest using different ad codes. You can later go to the performance report and analyze the individual revenue.</p>\n<h2>In-Feed FAQ</h2>\n<h3>How many In-feed ads should I place?</h3>\n<p>AdSense does not suggest a specific amount of In-feed ads on your WordPress site, but there is still some limitation. There shouldn’t be too many ads too close together.</p>\n<p>If you have long and full posts on your archive pages, then you could place an ad between all of them. If you show only short excerpts, then I would not recommend to place an ad before every post.</p>\n<p>Our tests also have shown that the ads before the first articles perform best and very often ads before the bottom posts perform only very little or not at all. Save your site some bandwidth and don’t place more ads there.</p>\n<h3>Where can I place an In-feed ad?</h3>\n<p>You are allowed to place the ad above, below or within the list of posts, but not in your sidebar or the header next to your logo.</p>\n<h3>When is the AdSense In-feed visible?</h3>\n<p>Like with all new AdSense ad units, it might take up to 30 minutes until the ad is showing up on your site. With new accounts, it might even take a bit longer.</p>\n<h2>Placing other ad types between posts</h2>\n<p>Would you like to put not only AdSense In-feed ads between posts? In this case, check out the <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/placement-post-lists/\">Post List Placement</a>. It works with all kinds of ads.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-adsense-in-feed-to-wordpress/\">How to add AdSense In-Feed to WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Advanced Ads Pro 2.0 released\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/advanced-ads-pro-2-0-released/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 24 Oct 2017 08:20:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Update Notices\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=85846\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:564:\"<p>Advanced Ads Pro version 2.0 comes with new and powerful features to improve performance, gain revenues and make your ads safer. In case you run into any problems with the update, please contact me through support. Show alternative ads to ad block users The wide use of ad blockers leads to decreasing revenues and can finally [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/advanced-ads-pro-2-0-released/\">Advanced Ads Pro 2.0 released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5154:\"<p>Advanced Ads Pro version 2.0 comes with new and powerful features to improve performance, gain revenues and make your ads safer.</p>\n<p>In case you run into any problems with the update, please contact me through <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/support/\">support</a>.</p>\n<h2>Show alternative ads to ad block users</h2>\n<p>The wide use of ad blockers leads to decreasing revenues and can finally cause a serious problem for websites which are monetarized by display ads. While it is not always possible to show the same ad to ad block users, you can still use the available space to engage or even monetize them.</p>\n<p>While the basic version of Advanced Ads comes with an option to count visitors using an ad blocker, Advanced Ads Pro allows you to select an alternative ad for each placement to show up if the visitor uses an ad blocker.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-84260\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content-679x281.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"679\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content-679x281.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content-300x124.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content-60x25.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content-150x62.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/AdBlocker-alternative-content.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Here you can find an overview of all<a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/ad-blockers/\"><strong> ad blocker related features</strong></a>.</p>\n<h2>Lazy Load ads</h2>\n<p>Lazy Load is a technology that prevents loading elements on a website before they would appear in the visible area of the browser window. This keeps the loading time to a minimum and improves its performance. What is very common for images is with Advanced Ads Pro 2.0 now also available for ads.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-84561 size-full\" title=\"Reduce load time and improve performance with Lazy Load for ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png\" alt=\"Reduce load time with Lazy Load for ads\" width=\"600\" height=\"161\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png 600w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-300x81.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-60x16.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-150x40.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In this tutorial, you can learn more about <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/lazy-load-ads/\"><strong>lazy loading ads</strong></a>.</p>\n<h2>Click Fraud Protection</h2>\n<p>Click fraud is happening when someone clicks on an ad who is not interested in its content while on the other end, an advertiser is paying for that click. You can imagine that ad networks, like AdSense, and also clients who purchase ad space on your site might have a problem with that.</p>\n<p>Advanced Ads Pro comes with a Click Fraud Protection feature to hide ads when a user clicks too often on them.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-83998 size-full\" title=\"Click Fraud Protection with Advanced Ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options.png\" alt=\"Default click fraud protection options\" width=\"474\" height=\"101\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options.png 474w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options-300x64.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options-60x13.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/click-fraud-protection-options-150x32.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px\" /></a></p>\n<p>We also added a similar Visitor Condition called <em>Max. Ad Clicks</em>, which allows you to define the maximum amount of clicks a single user can make on an ad before removing it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Read more about <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/click-fraud-protection/\"><strong>Click Fraud Protection</strong></a> on this page.</p>\n<h2>Get Advanced Ads Pro 2.0</h2>\n<p>Not a Pro user, yet? Similar click fraud solutions cost more than twice than Advanced Ads Pro, and you get plenty of additional features. Check out <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Pro features and pricing</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/advanced-ads-pro-2-0-released/\">Advanced Ads Pro 2.0 released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"How to add the Facebook Pixel to WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-add-facebook-pixel-to-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 23 Oct 2017 13:48:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Facebook Pixel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=86177\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:589:\"<p>Facebook’s retargeting technology helps you to track conversions and build custom audiences to better target your Facebook ads. To get started, you need to implement the Facebook Pixel to your website. In this tutorial, you are going to learn how to do that in WordPress using Advanced Ads. Create and get the Facebook Pixel The [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-add-facebook-pixel-to-wordpress/\">How to add the Facebook Pixel to WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5905:\"<p>Facebook’s retargeting technology helps you to track conversions and build custom audiences to better target your Facebook ads. To get started, you need to implement the Facebook Pixel to your website. In this tutorial, you are going to learn how to do that in WordPress using Advanced Ads.</p>\n<h2>Create and get the Facebook Pixel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel.png\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-86221 size-medium\" title=\"Create the Facebook Pixel\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel-300x280.png\" alt=\"How to create the Facebook Pixel\" width=\"300\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel-300x280.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel-679x634.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel-60x56.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel-150x140.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Get-the-Facebook-Pixel.png 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>The very first step you need to do is to login in to your Facebook account and switch to the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ads/manager\" rel=\"nofollow\">ads manager</a>.</p>\n<p>Open the tools section and click on <em>Pixel</em> to create your own Facebook Pixel. Enter a name for it and then press the <em>Create a Pixel</em> button to continue.</p>\n<p>Afterwards, a popup window will appear where you can choose if you want to email the pixel code to your technical manager or if you want to install it yourself.</p>\n<p>Click on this option (<em>Manually Install the Code Yourself</em>) and simply copy the Facebook Pixel code with your unique ID that Facebook will show you with the next window.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-86226 aligncenter\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"541\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress.png 1024w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress-300x158.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress-679x359.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress-60x32.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/add-facebook-pixel-to-WordPress-150x79.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>Implement the Facebook Pixel</h2>\n<p>To set up the Facebook Pixel, we need at least one ad unit and one placement.</p>\n<p>Go to <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Ads &gt; Create New Ad</em></p>\n<p>Select the ad type <em>plain text and code</em> if it is not already pre-selected and insert the code from your clipboard.</p>\n<p>Give your ad a title. We called ours &#8220;Facebook Pixel&#8221;.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-86229 size-full\" title=\"Inject the Facebook Pixel into WordPress\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads.png\" alt=\"Implement the Facebook Pixel in WordPress\" width=\"1100\" height=\"683\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads.png 1100w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads-300x186.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads-679x422.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads-60x37.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Inplement-Facebook-Pixel-Advanced-Ads-150x93.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" /></a></p>\n<p>After you published this ad, create a new placement for it.</p>\n<p>Go to <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Placements</em> and choose either the header or the footer code placement from the list and your just created ad unit as the item.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-86230 alignright\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/header-footer-code-placement.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"112\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/header-footer-code-placement.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/header-footer-code-placement-60x22.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/header-footer-code-placement-150x56.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></p>\n<p>The impact of the Facebook Pixel on the load time of your website is negligible so you can put the code into your header. But if you want to load this script in your footer, you can do that too. It is working on this position as well.</p>\n<p>After you have created the placement and selected your ad unit, the Facebook Pixel is successfully added to your website, and you can start to build Lookalike Audiences from your visitors. The pixel does not add anything visible on your website. It saves a browser cookie for retargeting or remarketing and tracks custom conversions.</p>\n<p>If you are based in the EU, you will finally need to update your <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/display-eu-cookie-law-compliant-info-message/\"><strong>Cookie Law compliant Info Message</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-add-facebook-pixel-to-wordpress/\">How to add the Facebook Pixel to WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"How to lazy load ads in WordPress?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/lazy-load-ads/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 12 Oct 2017 14:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=84559\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:528:\"<p>Lazy Load is a technology to prevent that objects on a website are getting loaded before they would appear in the visible area of the visitor. This keeps the loading time of a website at a minimum and improves its performance. Lazy loading is a very common concept to handle images. We developed a Lazy [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/lazy-load-ads/\">How to lazy load ads in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3650:\"<p>Lazy Load is a technology to prevent that objects on a website are getting loaded before they would appear in the visible area of the visitor. This keeps the loading time of a website at a minimum and improves its performance. Lazy loading is a very common concept to handle images.</p>\n<p>We developed a Lazy Load feature to provide a solution for a deferred loading of all kind of ads.</p>\n<h2>How does Lazy Load work for ads?</h2>\n<p>The principle of Lazy Load for ads is to load the content or scripts when the user scrolls to the position where the ad should be visible.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> has this feature on the placement level. Before you can activate this function for single placements, you will need to enable the module by clicking on <em>Activate lazy load module</em> in <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Settings &gt; Pro</em>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-84562 size-full\" title=\"How to enable Lazy Load in Advanced Ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads.png\" alt=\"Lazy Load moduel Advanced Ads\" width=\"477\" height=\"41\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads.png 477w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads-300x26.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads-60x5.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-Advanced-Ads-150x13.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 477px) 100vw, 477px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Now, you can activate Lazy Load for every placement. A typical use case is an AdSense unit that is being injected into a placement at the end of all articles. Activated Lazy Load would improve the loading time of that site because the time-consuming call for the AdSense ad will only happen when the visitor scrolls to the end of the article and not when he first opens the site. Enabling Lazy Load for AdSense ads on those positions has a very positive impact on the Active View rates and can result in higher revenues.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-84561 size-full\" title=\"Reduce load time and improve performance with Lazy Load for ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png\" alt=\"Reduce load time with Lazy Load for ads\" width=\"600\" height=\"161\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads.png 600w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-300x81.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-60x16.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/lazyload-ads-150x40.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>What else you need to know</h2>\n<p>The Lazy Load feature is only available for the following placements: Before Content, Content, After Content, Sidebar Widget, Post List and Manual Placement. It is not provided for PopUps and sticky ads and for the following placements: Above Headline, Custom Position, Content Middle, Random Position, Genesis, BuddyPress and bbPress.</p>\n<p>Tracking of lazy loaded ads is using an AJAX request for every ad. These requests might need additional performance on your site.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/lazy-load-ads/\">How to lazy load ads in WordPress?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"How to integrate Amazon ads, widgets and Amazon OneLink in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-amazon-ads/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 12 Oct 2017 09:24:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=84008\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:579:\"<p>The Amazon Associates Program is one of the largest and most successful networks for affiliates who recommend and sell products. There are several ways to create and display ads for it. This tutorial will show how you can use Advanced Ads to manage Amazon ads on your site. Amazon OneLink Amazon OneLink is a simple [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-amazon-ads/\">How to integrate Amazon ads, widgets and Amazon OneLink in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8266:\"<p>The Amazon Associates Program is one of the largest and most successful networks for affiliates who recommend and sell products. There are several ways to create and display ads for it. This tutorial will show how you can use Advanced Ads to manage Amazon ads on your site.</p>\n<h2>Amazon OneLink</h2>\n<p>Amazon OneLink is a simple way to cover users from different countries with the same link. This international traffic is getting redirected to the country-specific Amazon sites with the correct sales tracking code for that region.</p>\n<p>To implement this technology on your site you need to inject the OneTag script. This script checks every link to detect Amazon links including banners, widgets, image links and Amazon shortlinks.</p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_84179\" style=\"max-width: 679px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"wp-image-84179 size-large\" title=\"Copy the OneTag code from your Amazon dashboard\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink-679x152.png\" alt=\"Amazon OneLink\" width=\"679\" height=\"152\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink-679x152.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink-300x67.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink-60x13.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink-150x34.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/amazon-onelink.png 750w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Copy the OneTag code from your Amazon dashboard</figcaption></figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After you configured your OneLink settings in your account, you will get a customized code that needs to get injected throughout your whole website. The easiest way to do that is to create a new ad in Advanced Ads (ad type: plain text and code), to insert the OneTag there and to send this to a footer placement that you create as well.</p>\n<p>Currently, Amazon Onelink is only available for US, Canada, and the UK. You can find more information about OneLink settings in the <a href=\"https://affiliate-program.amazon.com/help/node/topic/202164400?cid=onelinkfaq2&amp;ac-ms-src=onelinkfaq2\" rel=\"nofollow\">official integration guide</a>.</p>\n<p>Links that have been created by third-party link shorteners (for example Pretty Links or the Advanced Ads Tracking) are currently not supported and will not get redirected through OneLink.</p>\n<h2>Use and display the official Amazon widgets</h2>\n<p>In your Amazon account you can also find tools to build and layout your own widgets. But before you start to customize them, you will need to choose one out of different basic widget types like deals, search boxes, my favorites, carousels, slideshows, mp3 widgets, recommended products or self-optimizing links.</p>\n<p>You will be guided step by step through the following building progress. Finally, you can copy the widget code and paste it into a new ad unit of Advanced Ads. Please use the „plain text and code“ ad type for this code as well.</p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_84010\" style=\"max-width: 679px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-84010 size-large\" title=\"How to integrate Amazon Widgets into Advanced Ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads-679x252.jpg\" alt=\"Use the “plain text and code” ad type to manage the official Amazon widgets\" width=\"679\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads-679x252.jpg 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads-300x111.jpg 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads-60x22.jpg 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads-150x56.jpg 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon-Widget-Advanced-Ads.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Use the &#8220;plain text and code&#8221; ad type to manage the official Amazon widgets</figcaption></figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After you published the ad you can select the placements where you want to display it on your site.</p>\n<h2>Inject tables and product lists with shortcodes</h2>\n<p>Much more attractive than the official widgets are product tables and lists that can be created with dedicated plugins like Amazon Affiliate Plugin for WordPress (AAWP), Amazon Link, Amazon Product in a Post, Amazon JS, Amazon Auto Links, AmazonSimpleAdmin (ASA), AmazonSimpleAffiliate (ASA2), or the official <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/amazon-associates-link-builder/\">Amazon Associates Link Builder</a> plugin.</p>\n<p>With such plugins, you can create for example product widgets, comparative tables or bestseller lists and integrate them with shortcodes into your website. As long as you use the „rich content“ ad type Advanced Ads is able to interpret these shortcodes and display the content. That&#8217;s why Advanced Ads is perfectly suited for a combined use together with those plugins.</p>\n<p><em>Note: If you have an active license for any Advanced Ads product, you can find a 20% discount code for the well made <a href=\"https://getaawp.com\">AAWP plugin</a> in your <span class=\"paragraph\"><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/account/\">account</a></span>.</em></p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_84009\" style=\"max-width: 679px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-84009 size-large\" title=\"Manage content of the Amazon Associates Link Builder\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder-679x277.jpg\" alt=\"Use the &quot;rich content&quot; ad type to display tables and product lists of dedicated Amazon plugins\" width=\"679\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder-679x277.jpg 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder-300x123.jpg 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder-60x25.jpg 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder-150x61.jpg 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Amazon_Associates_Link_Builder.jpg 999w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Use the &#8220;rich content&#8221; ad type to display tables and product lists of dedicated Amazon plugins</figcaption></figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once you have created your tables and widgets, you can send them automatically to your placements. The main advantage of injecting those shortcodes with Advanced Ads is the capability to optimize the ads for specific content as well as for individual users. For example, you could show different tables to your desktop and mobile visitors or you could display specific products in posts of corresponding categories.</p>\n<h2>Advanced Ads suppresses the automatically added attributes to text links</h2>\n<p>Since WordPress 4.7.4 the „noopener“ and „noreferrer“ attributes are added automatically by the WordPress editor to all your links in your posts. These attributes can prevent a sale being attributed to the affiliate account and prevent the payout of the commission.</p>\n<p>Basically, the ads that are created with Advanced Ads have the same technical structure like posts. If you are used to working with text links, you will be happy to hear that Advanced Ads suppresses the automatic insertion of the „noopener“ and „noreferrer“ attributes in our own ad types, not only Amazon ads.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-amazon-ads/\">How to integrate Amazon ads, widgets and Amazon OneLink in WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"How to manage ads on membership sites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-ads-on-membership-sites/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 19 Jun 2017 13:22:11 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"Paid Memberships Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=65348\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:551:\"<p>Closed community- and membership areas are a proven way to share your content with a chosen audience. With Advanced Ads Pro you can simply manage your ads on those membership sites as well as target your ads in relation to the membership level of your visitors. In this tutorial you will learn: How to set [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-ads-on-membership-sites/\">How to manage ads on membership sites</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10644:\"<p>Closed community- and membership areas are a proven way to share your content with a chosen audience. With <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> you can simply manage your ads on those membership sites as well as target your ads in relation to the membership level of your visitors.</p>\n<p><strong>In this tutorial you will learn:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to set up a membership site</li>\n<li>How to manage ads on closed membership areas</li>\n<li>How to target users with different membership levels</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to set up a membership site</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/paid-memberships-pro-checkbox.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-65359\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/paid-memberships-pro-checkbox.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"291\" height=\"247\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/paid-memberships-pro-checkbox.png 291w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/paid-memberships-pro-checkbox-60x51.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/paid-memberships-pro-checkbox-150x127.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 291px) 100vw, 291px\" /></a>One of the most popular solutions to create membership areas on a WordPress is the free plugin <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/paid-memberships-pro/\">Paid Memberships Pro</a>. Advanced Ads Pro automatically integrates with this plugin.</p>\n<p>The first steps with Paid Memberships Pro are quite easy. After the plugin is activated, you can define different membership levels. They will allow you to enable or disable the access to content, which is tagged for specific membership levels.</p>\n<p>The example on the image shows three different membership levels: „Free“, „Supporter“ und „Premium Membership“.</p>\n<p>The membership plugin adds a checkbox to the edit screen of content like categories, pages or posts. Using them, you can define the specific membership level necessary to access it. Unregistered users or those with insufficient memberships will see a corresponding note instead of the content.</p>\n<h2>How to manage ads on closed membership areas</h2>\n<p>With Advanced Ads Pro you can use the display condition „PMP Page Level“ to show or hide ads on membership sites. After you selected the condition you can choose the available membership levels from a list. Doing so, you can define exactly whether ads should be displayed on sites which require a specific membership level or not.</p>\n<h3>Example 1: How to deactivate ads on membership sites</h3>\n<p>Use the following setting to hide ads for all visitors on all sites of a closed membership area.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-65355 size-large\" title=\"Hide all ads on membership sites\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads-679x204.png\" alt=\"Display condition for Paid Memberships Pro\" width=\"679\" height=\"204\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads-679x204.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads-300x90.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads-60x18.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads-150x45.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membership-display-condition-Advanced-Ads.png 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Example 2: Display an ad only on specific pages of a membership area</h3>\n<p>Let&#8217;s stay with our previous example but now, we want to hide the same ad on sites which require the memberships „Supporter“ and „Premium“. Furthermore, we are going to display it on all sites of the membership area which require the „Free Membership“. To achieve this, just select those page types from the list on which you want to show the ad.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-65354 size-large\" title=\"Display Condition for Advanced Ads to manage ads on membership sites\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro-679x210.png\" alt=\"Manage ads in Paid Memberships Pro\" width=\"679\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro-679x210.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro-300x93.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro-60x19.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro-150x47.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/display-condition-paid-memberships-pro.png 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>How to target users with different membership levels</h2>\n<p>Paid Memberships Pro adds a new role to all registered users If you use the visitor condition “PMP User Level“ Advanced Ads will identify this user role and can show or hide an ad depending on the visitor’s membership level.</p>\n<h3>Example 3: Hide all ads for registered users</h3>\n<p>You can use the visitor condition “PMP User Level“ to hide ads for users with a registered membership level on those pages that don&#8217;t require any memberships with the following configuration.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-65356 size-large\" title=\"Advanced Ads provides a visitor condition to control ads on membership sites\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-679x276.png\" alt=\"Visitor Condition to manage ads on membership sites\" width=\"679\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-679x276.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-300x122.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-60x24.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-150x61.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads.png 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Example 4: Hide ads for specific memberships</h3>\n<p>To hide ads from specific user groups (these are in our example „Support“ and „Premium Membership“) but to show them to other members you need to select the corresponding user levels like following.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-65357 size-large\" title=\"Visitor Condition of Advanced Ads to control ads on membership sites\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2-679x268.png\" alt=\"ads on WordPress sites with membership\" width=\"679\" height=\"268\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2-679x268.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2-300x118.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2-60x24.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2-150x59.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example2.png 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Example 5: Display ads for specific memberships</h3>\n<p>Of course it is possible to reverse this scenario and to display targeted ads to specific user groups. A use case for this setting could be an offer to free registered users to upgrade their memberships.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-65358 size-large\" title=\"Targeted ads to specific user groups on membership sites\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3-679x276.png\" alt=\"Display targeted ads to specific user groups on membership sites\" width=\"679\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3-679x276.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3-300x122.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3-60x24.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3-150x61.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/membershipvisitor-condition-Advanced-Ads-example3.png 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>Issues and limitations</h2>\n<p>Ad management on closed areas of membership sites is currently just working if those sites are created and administrated with the free plugin Paid Memberships Pro. Other membership plugins are currently not supported with a specific display or visitor conditions by Advanced Ads.</p>\n<p>The different user levels of Paid Memberships Pro are not hierarchically structured. Therefore you’ll need to consider all different membership levels in your ad configurations.</p>\n<p>If you want to use the visitor condition &#8220;PMP User Level&#8221; on WordPress installations where you also run a caching solution, you will need to activate the cache busting feature in <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> to make it work reliably.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manage-ads-on-membership-sites/\">How to manage ads on membership sites</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"How to stop AdSense ads appearing in random positions (QuickStart)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/adsense-in-random-positions-quickstart/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 08 Jun 2017 10:50:21 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=65838\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:467:\"<p>Do ads seem to appear randomly on your website? If you are using AdSense then this is probably caused by their new QuickStart feature. Find out more about that and how to fix it in this article.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/adsense-in-random-positions-quickstart/\">How to stop AdSense ads appearing in random positions (QuickStart)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Thomas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4649:\"<p>In the last weeks we received many emails from users reporting AdSense ads appearing randomly on their sites. Some even disabled Advanced Ads and still saw those ads. Either way, in all cases the irritation was not caused Advanced Ads, but a major change in AdSense. However, there is something we did about this anyway.</p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_66518\" style=\"max-width: 315px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-66518\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/adsense-quickstart-hint.png\" alt=\"AdSense QuickStart warning by Advanced Ads\" width=\"315\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/adsense-quickstart-hint.png 315w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/adsense-quickstart-hint-291x300.png 291w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/adsense-quickstart-hint-58x60.png 58w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/adsense-quickstart-hint-145x150.png 145w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">The blue message was added by Advanced Ads to inform ad managers about automatically placed ads on your site.</figcaption></figure>\n<h2>Automatic ads with QuickStart</h2>\n<p>In early 2017, AdSense introduced <em>QuickStart</em>, a feature that placed AdSense ads automatically on websites. This move should have made the job of webmasters much easier, but caused a lot of confusion when ads appear in less optimized positions.</p>\n<p>For new AdSense accounts, <strong>QuickStart is enabled by default</strong> and since it is placed through the verification ad tag, which is also identical to the page level ad tag, it is easy to bring this to your website without knowing.</p>\n<p>While it is yet too early to say whether this feature is a benefit for publishers or a manual optimization of ad positions works better, using both options will only cause problems, since there might be too many ads on your site.</p>\n<p>Personally, we believe that placing the ads manually is a better basis for optimizing them, especially when you can <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-split-test-different-ad-positions/\">split test for positions</a>.</p>\n<h2>QuickStart warning in Advanced Ads</h2>\n<p>In version 1.7.26 of Advanced Ads we added a warning below all ads placed automatically with QuickStart – see the image on top of this article. This warning is <strong>only visible to logged in ad managers</strong>!</p>\n<p>In our experience, users who install and run Advanced Ads usually intend to control the position of their ads and running QuickStart ads and your own positions can cause conflicts.</p>\n<p>However, if you feel irritated by this warning you can disable all AdSense warnings in <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Settings &gt; AdSense</em>.</p>\n<h2>How to disable QuickStart?</h2>\n<p>In case you don’t want to see these ads on your site, you have different methods to remove them.</p>\n<h3>Disable the QuickStart option</h3>\n<p>You could just go to your AdSense account and search for <em>My Ads &gt; Page-level ads</em> in the main menu. When QuickStart is available for your account then you will find the appropriate option there and can disable it.</p>\n<p>There could be a short delay until the ads no longer appear.</p>\n<h3>Remove the ad code</h3>\n<p>Whether you still have the AdSense verification code enabled or you placed the Page-level ads code into the header of your site, since they are identical, you could remove it in order to also remove QuickStart.</p>\n<p>When you added this code with Advanced Ads then just go to <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Settings &gt; AdSense</em> and disable the <em>Activate Page-Level ads</em> option.</p>\n<p>This would also remove Page-level ads from your site, if you use them. Manually placed ad units are of course still going to work.</p>\n<p>If ads still appear then please flush the cache of your website, if you are using one, and make sure the AdSense verification tag or Page-level ads code was not placed with another method, e.g. directly into your theme, through a theme option or another plugin.</p>\n<h2>What else?</h2>\n<p>Established accounts should not even see the QuickStart feature. If there are still AdSense ads in random placements and you are using Advanced Ads then please <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/support/\">reach out to us for help</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/adsense-in-random-positions-quickstart/\">How to stop AdSense ads appearing in random positions (QuickStart)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Insert Ads between Posts in WordPress – 3 different methods\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 May 2017 13:15:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=63255\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:365:\"<p>How to insert ads between posts in WordPress with three methods provided by the Advanced Ads plugin.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress/\">Insert Ads between Posts in WordPress – 3 different methods</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Thomas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5728:\"<p>While inserting ads in the <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/post-ad-injection-placement/\">post content</a> is fairly easy, to insert ads between posts on your homepage, category pages or other archives is a bit more complicated. Advanced Ads has a couple of options to do that manually or automatically. This tutorial shows the simplest solutions our ad plugin for WordPress can current provide.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>AdSense In-feed between posts</li>\n<li>using a PHP function</li>\n<li>with the Post Lists placement</li>\n<li>with the Custom Positions placement</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Please find the explanation of each method below.</p>\n<h2>AdSense In-feed between posts</h2>\n<p>If you want to place the AdSense In-feed ad between posts on your WordPress site then place check out <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-adsense-in-feed-to-wordpress/\">this dedicated tutorial</a>.</p>\n<h2>Insert ads between posts manually in your template</h2>\n<p>With the basic version of Advanced Ads, you can create a <em>Manual Placement</em> and put it into the loop in template files like <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">home.php</pre> or <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">index.php</pre>. The function to go with is <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">the_ad_placement(\'your-placement-id\')</pre> .</p>\n<p>If you want to show the ad only between specific posts (e.g. the fourth and the fifth), you can use the code from below.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">// global $wp_query; // uncomment if loop content is in another file or function\nif( function_exists(\'the_ad_placement\') &amp;&amp; $wp_query-&gt;current_post === 4 ){ \n    the_ad_placement(\'your-placement-id\');\n}</pre><p>\n<em>your-placement-id</em> is the id of the placement you created. You get this by clicking on the <em>Usage</em> link in the placement table.</p>\n<p>Please make sure that you have access to your files via FTP and make a backup of the edited file, because a simple PHP error could break your site.</p>\n<p>If coding is not your strength then insert ads between posts with the Post Lists placement, which is explained below.</p>\n<h2>Inserting ads betwen posts automatically (most simple solution)</h2>\n<p>The most simple solution is to use the <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/placement-post-lists/\">Post Lists</a> placement. This is a placement we developed specifically to insert ads between posts. It works similar to the normal content injection.</p>\n<p>The Post Lists placement comes with <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> and can be found under <em>Advanced Ads &gt; Placements</em>. A simple setup might look like this:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-63256 size-full\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example.png\" alt=\"Post Lists placement setup\" width=\"847\" height=\"141\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example.png 847w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example-300x50.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example-679x113.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example-60x10.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/post-list-example-150x25.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 847px) 100vw, 847px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This placement is using WordPress standards. You can find more details about it on <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/placement-post-lists/\">this page</a>.</p>\n<p>If your post list is not based on the default loop or has some specific design then take a look at the Custom Position option below.</p>\n<h2>Using Custom Positions for advanced layouts</h2>\n<p>Some themes have specific layouts for all or some archive pages. This might be a grid on the homepage or an implementation of the post list that is not based on WordPress standards.</p>\n<p>In these situations, the <em>Custom Positions</em> placement might work better than <em>Post Lists</em> to insert ads between posts.</p>\n<p>The Custom Position is a placement that allows you to select any position for an ad. Hence, you can also choose a position between posts on your homepage or other archive pages.</p>\n<p>The example below shows the Custom Position settings after choosing the fourth element in a post list in the frontend.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-68655 size-full\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1.png\" alt=\"insert ads between posts in WordPress\" width=\"542\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1.png 542w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1-300x116.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1-60x23.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress-1-150x58.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Inserting the ad between posts with this placement might need some custom adjustments to your layout, especially, if this is a grid with a specific number of elements. Ask your frontend developer or the theme developers for help.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/insert-ads-between-posts-wordpress/\">Insert Ads between Posts in WordPress – 3 different methods</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"How to block ads on a specific page?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-block-ads-on-a-specific-page/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 25 Nov 2016 12:37:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=39458\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:391:\"<p>With Advanced Ads you can exclude ads from specific pages, e.g. to keep your legal pages ad free. The following article shows the two methods for this.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-block-ads-on-a-specific-page/\">How to block ads on a specific page?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Joachim\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4087:\"<p>With Advanced Ads you can exclude ads from specific posts and pages. E.g., you can keep your ads away from appearing on your contact or privacy policy pages. The following tutorial explains both methods that just need a few clicks.</p>\n<h2>Use display conditions to block individual ads on specific pages</h2>\n<p>With the „Specific Pages“ <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/manual/display-conditions/\">display condition</a> on the ad edit page you can enter the title or the ID of the site where this specific ad should or in our case shouldn’t appear. That’s all and you can check the results of your settings on your pages afterwards.</p>\n<p>In the following example you can see a setting for an ad that appears on all pages except “Contact” and “Places of interest”.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-39568 size-large\" title=\"Block ads on specific pages with Advanced Ads\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1-679x403.png\" alt=\"Disable ads on specific pages\" width=\"679\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1-679x403.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1-300x178.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1-60x36.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1-150x89.png 150w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-specific-pages-1.png 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This method is recommended, if you want to exclude single ads from specific pages, e.g., if you use ads for internal services and you want to disable them on your landing pages.</p>\n<h2>Disable all ads in specific pages</h2>\n<p>If you want to disable all ads on specific posts or pages, it is easier not to exclude them one by one with individual display conditions. In this case, you should look out for the Ad Settings meta box which you can find on the bottom of the edit page of every post and page. You will find a checkbox there which allows you to disable all ads on this page.</p>\n<p>If your are using <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a>, you will find a second option there to disable all ads inside the post content but not from the header, the footer or your sidebar.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-39462 size-full\" title=\"Disable ads inside the content with Advanced Ads Pro\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages.png\" alt=\"disable ads on pages\" width=\"440\" height=\"96\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages.png 440w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages-300x65.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages-60x13.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/disable-ads-on-pages-150x33.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This method is recommended, if you want to keep specific pages with less clicks or legal pages completely ad free.</p>\n<h2>Constant to hide ads</h2>\n<p>You can also hide all coming ads by setting the <pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">ADVADS_ADS_DISABLED</pre>  constant in your theme or plugin like in the code below.</p><pre class=\"crayon-plain-tag\">if(!defined(\'ADVADS_ADS_DISABLED\')){\n    define(\'ADVADS_ADS_DISABLED\', true);\n};</pre><p>\nOnce you set the constant, future loaded ads won’t be displayed.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/how-to-block-ads-on-a-specific-page/\">How to block ads on a specific page?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"How to add ads on BuddyPress pages?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-on-buddypress-pages/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Nov 2016 11:15:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=38528\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:359:\"<p>This tutorial explains how to display ads on BuddyPress pages and inject them into activity streams, group pages or other positions.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-on-buddypress-pages/\">How to add ads on BuddyPress pages?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Hans-Lukas Herse\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4479:\"<p>If you have ever tried building a community website using WordPress, you probably already know <a href=\"https://buddypress.org\">BuddyPress</a>. It is a WordPress plugin consisting of multiple components (e.g. groups, private messages, activity streams etc.), which allow you to build your own social network.</p>\n<p>Inserting ads on BuddyPress pages is difficult, because most of them are created dynamically. Automatic injections that work well for normal static pages and posts, are not working as expected on all BuddyPress related pages. Therefore, <a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> has placements dedicated exclusively to placing ads on BuddyPress pages.</p>\n<h2>How to display an ad on a BuddyPress page?</h2>\n<p>The placement dedicated to displaying ads on BuddyPress pages is the &#8220;BuddyPress Content&#8221; placement and you can find it in the list of placement types on the placement page.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38524 size-large\" title=\"BuddyPress Ad Placement\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement-679x200.png\" alt=\"BuddyPress Ad Placement\" width=\"679\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement-679x200.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement-300x88.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement-60x18.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Placement-150x44.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In order to set up an ad to display using the &#8220;BuddyPress Content&#8221; placement, you only need to select one of the multiple hooks from the &#8220;position&#8221; dropdown menu.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38523 size-large\" title=\"BuddyPress ad positions\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content-679x213.png\" alt=\"BuddyPress ad position select\" width=\"679\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content-679x213.png 679w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content-300x94.png 300w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content-60x19.png 60w, https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BuddyPress-Content-150x47.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Hooks listed under &#8220;Activity Entry&#8221; will display the ad in one of multiple positions in the BuddyPress activity streams on the pages &#8220;/activity&#8221;, &#8220;/members/username/&#8221; and &#8220;groups/groupname&#8221;.</p>\n<p>Hooks listed under &#8220;Groups List&#8221; and &#8220;Member List&#8221; will display an ad on the &#8220;/groups&#8221; and &#8220;/members&#8221; pages respectively.</p>\n<p>If you are unsatisfied with the positions provided by the hooks, you can also inject ads using the &#8220;Post Content&#8221; placement, however, this might take a basic understanding of your pages source code.</p>\n<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Why is the placement not showing up in my list?</p></blockquote>\n<p>In order to keep the list of placements as short as possible, the placement will only show up if the BuddyPress plugin is activated.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Why are my ads cut on certain pages?</p></blockquote>\n<p>We are merely injecting the ads into the positions provided by BuddyPress, so ads will be cut when they exceed the width of the container they are injected in. Please be sure to choose the correct format for your ads.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Why are my ads not showing up on group pages?</p></blockquote>\n<p>This is due to the fact that pages like &#8220;/groups/name&#8221; or &#8220;/members/name&#8221; are only virtual pages created by BuddyPress and are technically handled as 404 error pages by WordPress. You can fix this issue by disabling the global option &#8220;<label>Disable ads on 404 error pages&#8221; in the Advanced Ads plugin settings. </label></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-on-buddypress-pages/\">How to add ads on BuddyPress pages?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"How to show ads on bbPress pages?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-in-bbpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Nov 2016 10:53:58 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Advanced Ads Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"https://wpadvancedads.com/?p=38518\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:345:\"<p>This tutorial explains how to add ads to bbPress forum pages and inside the dynamically created threads and posts of such forums.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-in-bbpress/\">How to show ads on bbPress pages?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Hans-Lukas Herse\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2888:\"<p>Setting up a forum software can be a really tiring endeavor, setting up ads to display on those new forum pages even more. The WordPress plugin <a href=\"https://bbpress.org\">bbPress</a> offers an easy solution to the first problem and provides you with the tools to set up your own forums fast and easy. Advanced Ads provides you with all the tools you need to set up your ads on those pages.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/add-ons/advanced-ads-pro/\">Advanced Ads Pro</a> has two placements to help you setting up ads on forum pages created by bbPress, they are called &#8220;bbPress Static Content&#8221; and &#8220;bbPress Reply Content&#8221;.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-Placements-.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38520 size-large\" title=\"bbpress Ad Placements\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-Placements--1024x301.png\" alt=\"bbpress Ad Placements\" width=\"980\" height=\"288\" /></a></p>\n<h2>How to display an ad on a bbPress page?</h2>\n<p>First of all you need to decide where you want your ad to show up. There are two different placements with multiple hooks to place your ads.</p>\n<p><strong>The bbPress static content placement</strong> provides hooks to inject ads into multiple positions on the /forums, /forums/name or /forums/topic/name pages generated by bbPress.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-static-hooks.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38522 size-large\" title=\"bbPress static hooks ad Placement\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-static-hooks-1024x355.png\" alt=\"bbpress static hooks ad Placement\" width=\"980\" height=\"340\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>The bbPress reply content placement</strong> provides hooks to inject your ads at the nth reply on /forums/topic/name pages.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-reply-hooks.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38521 size-large\" title=\"bbPress Ads – reply hooks\" src=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/bbPress-reply-hooks-1024x212.png\" alt=\"bbPress reply hooks\" width=\"980\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\n<p>After choosing the appropriate placement, you only need to select the content you want to display and the hook you want to use from the dropdown menus.</p>\n<p>If you are unsatisfied with the positions provided by the hooks, you can also inject ads using the post content placement. However, this will require a basic understanding of the source code of the page you want to inject the ad into and the element to choose from the available options for the injection.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com/ads-in-bbpress/\">How to show ads on bbPress pages?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpadvancedads.com\">Advanced Ads</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:31:\"ht